  "name": "RPlog_Friendly_Interrogation",
  "title": "A Friendly Interrogation",
  "summary": "At NRI Headquarters, the Chiss agent Galin, accompanied by his R2 astromech Max, conducts the formal debriefing of recently rescued Ambassador Ambrosia Delgard following her ordeal in Imperial custody. Visibly broken in body and haunted, Ambrosia recounts the night the Caspian embassy was overrun: waking to the breaching mob, sending her daughter Gabi away with the Jedi Leo, holding off black-clad Imperial troops, and her eventual capture. She describes a grueling captivity aboard the Nemesis under interrogator Lord Aldus Thel, including sleep deprivation, a mock hanging, torture that destroyed her knees, and a moment of clinical death before being revived by the medical officer Dr. Liora Kovani. Ambrosia reveals that Thel ultimately extracted her confession by threatening Gabi's life, and that Kovani is an Imperial brainwashing victim with false memories. Increasingly bitter, she insists someone within the Republic rigged the CDU aid with spy equipment and got her killed, demanding accountability before limping out, requesting access to visit Kovani.",
